Section.name: About APCOER
Section.description:
ABMS Parishad’s Anantrao Pawar College of Engineering and Research (ABMSPCOER), Pune is the outcome of dedicated and well known educationalists and socially conscious people who empathised with the plight of less fortunate and oppressed people and spurred into action, establishing a new era of quality and unbiased education which is carried forward today by ABMSPCOER. The noble vision to empower the economically backward section through a system of value-based education, coupled with the mission to produce graduates highly skilled for employability or to be entrepreneurs, nurtures students in all spheres of life. Effectively using engineering knowledge for society’s benefit, ABMSPCOER establishes the right foundations for technical and humane learning.
Year Of Establishment
1907
Type
Private
Departments
Electronics and Telecom, Computer, Information Technology, Mechanical, Civil
Library
3809 books and 34 journals related to various streams, separate reading, reference, reprography section, etc.
Hostel
Hostel facility for boys and girls on campus for 100 nos. each.
Sports and Gym complex
Imported and indigenous gym and various sports’ equipment.
Campus
7.5 acres barrier-free space with medical facilities, uninterrupted power supply, 24 hr. Wi-Fi internet.
Activities
Vidhyarthini munch for promotion of women’s activities, swimming pool with separate students and staff timings, banking, a/c auditorium, etc.
How to Reach
189 km from Mumbai,20 km from Lohagaon Airport, 2 Km from Swargate Bus Stand,8 Km from Shivajinagar Railway Station & Bus Stand, 4 Km from Deccan Gymkhana.
